userStories.description:
Create `src/data/editor-tiles.ts` — a registry of ALL tiles available in the editor.

```typescript
export interface EditorTile {
  readonly id: string;           // e.g. 'emerald:ground-grass-light'
  readonly source: 'emerald' | 'frlg' | 'pmd';
  readonly category: 'ground' | 'water' | 'nature' | 'buildings' | 'decoration';
  readonly name: string;         // display name, e.g. 'Grass Light'
  readonly path: string;         // asset path relative to public/
  readonly width: number;        // in tiles (1 for normal, 2-3 for buildings)
  readonly height: number;       // in tiles
  readonly tileSize: number;     // 16 (GBA) or 24 (PMD)
  readonly collision: boolean;   // true = solid wall
  readonly destructible: boolean; // true = breakable
}

export const EDITOR_TILES: readonly EditorTile[] = [ ... ];

export function getTilesBySource(source: string): readonly EditorTile[] { ... }
export function getTilesByCategory(category: string): readonly EditorTile[] { ... }
export function getTileById(id: string): EditorTile | undefined { ... }
```

Populate with ALL extracted tiles from US-001, US-002, US-003. Scan `public/assets/tiles/` directories to build the list.

Update `src/scenes/BootScene.ts` to dynamically load all editor tiles:
```typescript
import { EDITOR_TILES } from '../data/editor-tiles';
// In preload():
for (const tile of EDITOR_TILES) {
  this.load.image(tile.id, tile.path);
}
```

Keep the existing tile loading for the current Emerald theme (tile-emerald-grass-light, etc.) — these are used by WorldSystem.

Must compile with `npx tsc --noEmit`.

Modify WorldSystem to support loading maps from JSON data.

Add to `src/systems/GameContext.ts`:
- `mapId: string | null` field (default: null = random/procedural)

Create `src/data/maps/` directory for map JSON files.

Create type definition:
```typescript
// In src/types.ts or new file src/data/maps/map-types.ts
export interface GameMap {
  name: string;
  version: number;
  width: number;
  height: number;
  tileSize: number;
  terrain: Record<string, string>;  // 'col,row' → biome/tile ID
  objects: Array<{ type: string; x: number; y: number; size?: [number, number]; source?: string }>;
  markers: Array<{ type: string; x: number; y: number; w?: number; h?: number; config?: Record<string, unknown> }>;
}
```

Modify `WorldSystem.generateWorld()`:
1. Accept optional `mapData: GameMap | null` parameter
2. If mapData is provided:
   - Use mapData.width × mapData.height for grid size
   - For each cell: check `mapData.terrain['col,row']`
     - If value starts with source prefix (e.g. 'emerald:'): use as exact tile ID
     - If value is a biome name ('forest', 'lake', etc.): run noise within that biome context
     - If no entry: use default noise (grassland)
3. If mapData is null: current behavior (100% procedural)

In GameScene.create(), pass mapData to WorldSystem:
```typescript
if (ctx.mapId) {
  const mapModule = await import(`../data/maps/map-${ctx.mapId}.json`);
  worldSystem.generateWorld(theme, mapModule.default);
} else {
  worldSystem.generateWorld(theme, null);
}
```

Zero breaking change: without mapId, game works exactly as before.

Must compile with `npx tsc --noEmit`.
